news.title: Flexible workspaces register 12.4 million sq ft of gross leasing volume in 2024
news.para: Bengaluru led with 3.4 million sq ft of leasing volume followed by Mumbai, which recorded 1.9 million sq ft GLV. Delhi-NCR registered 2.3 million, Hyderabad was at 1.6 million sq ft and Pune saw 1.6 million sq ft GLV.

news.title: Zaheer Khan, wife purchase apartment in Mumbai for Rs 11 crore
news.para: The apartment spans a carpet area of 2,158 sq ft (200.47 sq meters) and a built-up area of 240.58 sq meters (2,590 sq ft) and comes with three car parking spaces.

news.title: Arvind SmartSpaces acquires 150 acre project in Ahmedabad
news.para: Arvind SmartSpaces' project has a total estimated area of 150 acre and a top-line potential of Rs 600 crore.

news.title: Merlin Group to invest Rs 800 crore for second thematic project in Kolkata
news.para: ​Merlin has partnered with global lifestyle network FTV for the project. This will be Merlin's first brandedproject under F Residences. As part of the partnership, FTV will design the interior and exterior of the flats.

news.title: Revenue camps to address land-related issues in Bokaro
news.para: ​DC Jadhav Vijaya Narayan Rao has announced three-day camps across all halkas in the district from February 18 to March 4, 2025.

news.title: Mumbai: 20 years on, Mhada reclaims eight-acre Juhu plot from builder
news.para: The plot is located in a prime area opposite Ritambhara College, and its market value is said to be around Rs 2,000 crore.

news.title: Over 200 Supertech employees finally get salary for December 2024
news.para: The payment adheres to the plan prepared and submitted by interim resolution professional (IRP) Hitesh Goel in consultation with the Apex Court Committee (ACC), which oversaw the process.

news.title: Kalyan Dombivli civic body to raze 65 buildings on HC order
news.para: These buildings were declared illegal after developers constructed them using fake building plans and forged Rera certificates. About 6,500 homebuyers are likely to be affected.

news.title: Use of foreign companies to buy properties in UK under ED lens
news.para: While resident individuals are allowed to remit up to $250,000 a year to directly purchase properties abroad, acquiring stocks of foreign companies that primarily hold properties is a violation of foreign exchange regulations.

news.title: Noida: Over 1,400 SDS NRI Township buyers protest against builder's additional compensation demand
news.para: This demand by SDS Infracon will translate into an unexpected financial burden of around Rs 8-10 lakh for each buyer, despite a majority of them still lacking legal possession of their plots in the 125-acre township after more than a decade.

news.title: NCR builders shrink home sizes in affordability push
news.para: However, this year, many developers are considering launching flats with a starting size of 1,500 sq ft to ensure prices remain between ₹2-4 crore, said industry leaders.

news.title: Mumbai Police arrest builder in New India Citizen Cooperative Bank case
news.para: According to officials, Mehta and an unidentified accomplice allegedly conspired to siphon off the massive sum between May 2019 and January 2025.

news.title: Over 8,000 complaints pending with Maharashtra RERA
news.para: With around 8,000 complaints pending, besides delay in or non-execution of some of the regulator's orders, including recovery warrants by revenue authorities, experts say it "lacks teeth and needs to do more".

news.title: Begin construction of Indiramma houses: Telangana deputy CM tells officials
news.para: At a pre-budget review with the officials of the two departments, Bhatti said CM A Revanth Reddy stated that the construction of Indiramma houses should start immediately in Mahabubnagar and Rangareddy districts too, where the MLC poll code is not in force.

news.title: Enzyme Office Spaces lease out 14,000 sq ft space to SUGAR Cosmetics
news.para: Enzyme Office Spaces founder and CEO Ashish Agarwal said the company has given on lease 14,000 square feet workspace to SUGAR Cosmetics at its facility in Andheri East, Mumbai.

news.title: Telangana government land worth Rs 60,000 crore in ownership tussle
news.para: Located in high-demand and high-value areas such as Hafeezpet, Madhapur, and Kondapur, this land is at the centre of a legal battle with private firms and individuals claiming ownership.

news.title: Telangana launches LiDAR survey for 'One Map Hyderabad’ project
news.para: The ambitious light detection and ranging (LiDAR) survey will cover a range of crucial infrastructure details, including road network, water supply, electricity, sewage, and even fire and traffic police networks.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Pay property tax in advance, get up to 15% rebate in 2025-26
news.para: The decision was made while approving the civic body's Rs 15,502 crore budget for 2025-26. According to AMC, the advance payment rebate increased to 12% from the current 10%.

news.title: Asian Paints to exit Indonesia in nearly $6 million deal
news.para: Asian Paints said early last year that pursuing growth in Indonesia was "tough" due to profitability and cost control being under pressure.

news.title: Sebi proposes disclosure of financial information in offer documents for REITs, InvITs
news.para: These changes are based on the recommendations from the Working Group on Ease of Doing Business for REITs and InvITs, inputs from the Indian REITs Association and Bharat InvITs Association, and internal deliberations, Sebi said.
